RepostBy @romeo_and_brix: "RESCUES PLEASE HELP PARTNER!
.
SAVE JEROME! Public must #adopt or #foster this dog BEFORE 12PM ET tomorrow 5-17-2017; otherwise he will be killed at #Brooklyn Center.
.
My name is #JEROME. My Animal ID #A1111941. I am a male brown #brindle #american #pitbull terrier mix. The shelter thinks I am about 4 YEARS old. I came in the shelter as a STRAY on 05/13/2017. He is on the kill list due to his #injury of a broken pelvis or hip. He is in #pain and a New Hope Rescue needs to partner with the #adopter or #foster to save his life.
.
Upon intake Jerome was #receptive but #quiet for introduction as he may be #painful from an #injury. Jerome approached counselor and rested his head in lap for #petting. Counselor was able to scan for microchip (negative) collar and photograph.
.
ASSESSMENT:
.
Summary: Jerome was relaxed upon approach, but snaps once he came closer the helper dog.
.
PLAYGROUP: Jerome was surrendered as a #stray so his past behavior around dogs is unknown. Due to the extent of Jerome’s leg #injury, an off leash dog-dog interaction will not be conducted at this time.
.
MEDICAL BEHAVIOR: 5/13/17 Jerome was #calm. Do not tries to attack. Recommend muzzle due to #pain.
.
ENERGY LEVEL: We have no history on Jerome so we cannot be certain of his behavior in a home environment. Jerome displayed #low energy and movement throughout assessment. We recommend feeding with puzzle feeders and food-dispensing toys.
.
If you are local to the Tri-State, New England, and the general Northeast United States area, and you are SERIOUS about #adopting or #fostering, EMAIL helpdogs@urgentpodr.org. Experienced volunteers will do their best to guide you through the process." (via #InstaRepost @AppsKottage)

What an amazing night. Perfect Balance were represented at 9 Harley Street at the opening of the new CT Scanner.

The Clinic has invested just under £1M in the new CT scanner and client reception and changing areas which now exceed the standards of presentation of many of the Harley Street clinics.

The new unit was opened by Tessa Sanderson who attended, complete with her Olympic Gold medal. Toshiba Medical, who supplied the scanner to 9 Harley Street also provided imaging equipment to Tessa Sanderson’s Foundation.

Our Osteopath Julia and Director Daniel Law attended the event.

The view and the hill. On the heels of yesterday's post I am practicing what I preach. Today I changed up my route to include a beautiful relaxing view and finished my run with 5 sets of this hill. 
You won't get stronger or faster doing the same route at the same speed week after week. Try adding in 5 hill repeats to your run or simply sprint from one light post to the next few times in your run to challenge yourself that little bit more!

Hip Strategy
----------
Want to lessen your risk for injury when performing sport-related tasks such as landing or cutting?
. 
Learning to implement a 'hip strategy' when decelerating is thought to be an effective technique for taking advantage of the force generating capability of the large hip extensors (glutes) and knee extensors (quads) and decreasing overall stress to passive subsystem structures such as ligaments, cartilage and bone.
.
The hip strategy consists of three elements, which are depicted nicely in this video.
1️⃣ Flex the trunk
2️⃣ Flex the hips
3️⃣Avoid excessive anterior knee migration .
All of these strategies will help encourage force attenuation by the neuromuscular system and reduce injury risk and/or the development of pain.
.
.
.
